                        Agile, to be or not to be...
                    </div>
                    <div class="description">
                        I still remember the times of the Gantt diagrams. Maybe you never saw those but it was common in
                        big companies. A big project planned for years, with a couple of deadlines every 6 months or so
                        and a lot of useless overwork and stress when the deadlines were close. Depending on how much
                        the manager did care about the project she started to demand this sooner or later but I never
                        saw it working out.
                        <br><br>
                        Then companies started moving into Agile methodologies implementing frameworks like Scrum or
                        Kanban. Sometimes because one team member had knowledge or experience with the framework, other
                        times hiring expensive specialists like Scrum Masters or Agile Coaches.
                    </div>
